abstract: A senior U.S. diplomat on Monday called for Russia to free Paul Whelan, a former Marine accused by Moscow of espionage, saying there was no evidence against him and he had committed no crime.
snippet: A senior U.S. diplomat on Monday called for Russia to free Paul Whelan, a former Marine accused by Moscow of espionage, saying there was no evidence against him and he had committed no crime.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — A senior U.S. diplomat on Monday called for Russia to free Paul Whelan, a former Marine accused by Moscow of espionage, saying there was no evidence against him and he had committed no crime.
headline_main: U.S. Asks Russia to Free Incarcerated Ex-Marine Paul Whelan
headline_print_headline: U.S. Asks Russia to Free Incarcerated Ex-Marine Paul Whelan

abstract: Bosnian lawmakers approved a new central government on Monday after a 14-month deadlock, opening the way for a resumption of reforms needed to become a candidate for EU membership and for talks on a new deal with the International Monetary Fund.
snippet: Bosnian lawmakers approved a new central government on Monday after a 14-month deadlock, opening the way for a resumption of reforms needed to become a candidate for EU membership and for talks on a new deal with the International Monetary Fund.
lead_paragraph: SARAJEVO — Bosnian lawmakers approved a new central government on Monday after a 14-month deadlock, opening the way for a resumption of reforms needed to become a candidate for EU membership and for talks on a new deal with the International Monetary Fund.
headline_main: Bosnian Lawmakers Approve New Government After 14-Month Deadlock
headline_print_headline: Bosnian Lawmakers Approve New Government After 14-Month Deadlock

abstract: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi's party lost control of another state on Monday, adding to a string of electoral losses since last December amid protests that mark the biggest challenge to the Hindu-nationalist leader.
snippet: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi's party lost control of another state on Monday, adding to a string of electoral losses since last December amid protests that mark the biggest challenge to the Hindu-nationalist leader.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi's party lost control of another state on Monday, adding to a string of electoral losses since last December amid protests that mark the biggest challenge to the Hindu-nationalist leader.
headline_main: Modi Party Loses State Election Amid Protests Over Citizenship Law
headline_print_headline: Modi Party Loses State Election Amid Protests Over Citizenship Law

abstract: An international working group on the conflict in eastern Ukraine has agreed terms for a prisoner swap between Russia and Ukraine, Boris Gryzlov, Russia's envoy to the group, was cited by the RIA news agency as saying on Monday.
snippet: An international working group on the conflict in eastern Ukraine has agreed terms for a prisoner swap between Russia and Ukraine, Boris Gryzlov, Russia's envoy to the group, was cited by the RIA news agency as saying on Monday.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — An international working group on the conflict in eastern Ukraine has agreed terms for a prisoner swap between Russia and Ukraine, Boris Gryzlov, Russia's envoy to the group, was cited by the RIA news agency as saying on Monday.
headline_main: Russian Envoy Says Terms Agreed for New Prisoner Swap With Ukraine: RIA
headline_print_headline: Russian Envoy Says Terms Agreed for New Prisoner Swap With Ukraine: RIA

abstract: Heisman Trophy winner Joe Burrow is a hero on LSU's Baton Rouge campus, but he hasn't seen much of it because he took graduate courses online. Justin Fields rarely has to step inside an Ohio State classroom building because he also does most of his school work online to accommodate his grueling football schedule.
snippet: Heisman Trophy winner Joe Burrow is a hero on LSU's Baton Rouge campus, but he hasn't seen much of it because he took graduate courses online. Justin Fields rarely has to step inside an Ohio State classroom building because he also does most of hi...
lead_paragraph: COLUMBUS, Ohio — Heisman Trophy winner Joe Burrow is a hero on LSU's Baton Rouge campus, but he hasn't seen much of it because he took graduate courses online. Justin Fields rarely has to step inside an Ohio State classroom building because he also does most of his school work online to accommodate his grueling football schedule.
headline_main: Online Classes Keep Football Players Out of Academic Fray
headline_print_headline: Online Classes Keep Football Players Out of Academic Fray

abstract: This sacred river offers clues to the spread of one of the world’s most daunting health problems: germs impervious to common medicines.
snippet: This sacred river offers clues to the spread of one of the world’s most daunting health problems: germs impervious to common medicines.
lead_paragraph: GANGOTRI, India — High in the Himalayas, it’s easy to see why the Ganges River is considered sacred.

abstract: Arsenal have a squad that can be improved but the players must take up responsibility and be accountable for their actions on the pitch if they are to be a part of the club's future plans, new manager Mikel Arteta said on Monday.
snippet: Arsenal have a squad that can be improved but the players must take up responsibility and be accountable for their actions on the pitch if they are to be a part of the club's future plans, new manager Mikel Arteta said on Monday.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Arsenal have a squad that can be improved but the players must take up responsibility and be accountable for their actions on the pitch if they are to be a part of the club's future plans, new manager Mikel Arteta said on Monday.
headline_main: New Arsenal Boss Arteta Demands Accountability From Players
headline_print_headline: New Arsenal Boss Arteta Demands Accountability From Players

abstract: The consortium behind Nord Stream 2 said on Monday about 160 km (100 miles) of gas pipeline still needed to be laid, after a major contractor suspended work last week due to U.S. sanctions.
snippet: The consortium behind Nord Stream 2 said on Monday about 160 km (100 miles) of gas pipeline still needed to be laid, after a major contractor suspended work last week due to U.S. sanctions.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — The consortium behind Nord Stream 2 said on Monday about 160 km (100 miles) of gas pipeline still needed to be laid, after a major contractor suspended work last week due to U.S. sanctions.
headline_main: Nord Stream 2 Says 160 Km Left to Lay of Gas Pipeline to Europe
headline_print_headline: Nord Stream 2 Says 160 Km Left to Lay of Gas Pipeline to Europe

abstract: Manchester City boss Pep Guardiola said on Monday that he was planning to stay with the Premier League club next season amid talk that he would leave the champions at the end of the current campaign.
snippet: Manchester City boss Pep Guardiola said on Monday that he was planning to stay with the Premier League club next season amid talk that he would leave the champions at the end of the current campaign.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Manchester City boss Pep Guardiola said on Monday that he was planning to stay with the Premier League club next season amid talk that he would leave the champions at the end of the current campaign.
headline_main: Guardiola Looking Forward to Fifth Season With Man City
headline_print_headline: Guardiola Looking Forward to Fifth Season With Man City

abstract: A source close to Atlantia's motorway unit warned on Monday the company would go bankrupt if the government revoked its concession without compensation following the deadly collapse of a bridge last year.
snippet: A source close to Atlantia's motorway unit warned on Monday the company would go bankrupt if the government revoked its concession without compensation following the deadly collapse of a bridge last year.
lead_paragraph: ROME — A source close to Atlantia's motorway unit warned on Monday the company would go bankrupt if the government revoked its concession without compensation following the deadly collapse of a bridge last year.
headline_main: Italy's Motorway Operator Could Fail if Government Revokes License: Source
headline_print_headline: Italy's Motorway Operator Could Fail if Government Revokes License: Source
